    • Method Detail

      • terminate

        boolean terminate()
        Requests that the job be terminated. Not guaranteed to succeed. Returns true if the terminate might be handled, false if it will definitely not be handled.

      • processCommand

        void processCommand(Request cmd)
        Ask the executor to perform a command encapsulated in a Request. This was added to support capturing task stack traces while they are running, but it is general and may have other uses.
